PN,33305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781542111
OL,3,CLetters written by Hull-born William
OL,4,CWilberforce fetch #3.9k under the
OL,5,Chammer
OL,7,FThe first letter to Admiral Sir Sidney
OL,8,FSmith was written just after
OL,9,FNapoleon's first abdication after
OL,10,Fmilitary defeat.
OL,12,FThe letter highlights Wilberforce's
OL,13,Fefforts to expand the anti-slavery
OL,14,Fmovement to other nations. The letter
OL,15,Fdiscusses the Admiral's financial
OL,16,Ftroubles, from which Wilberforce says
OL,17,Fhe cannot bail him out as he himself
OL,18,Fis facing #2,000 of debt.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781542111
OL,3,CLetters written by Hull-born William
OL,4,CWilberforce fetch #3.9k under the
OL,5,Chammer
OL,7,FThe second letter in 1831, written two
OL,8,Fyears before his death, carries great
OL,9,Femotional weight. It's written to his
OL,10,Flong-time friend, the Marquis of
OL,11,FWellesley, and serves as a farewell.
OL,13,FAlso written are his own Christian
OL,14,Fepiphany and the driving force behind
OL,15,Fhis campaign to end slavery.
OL,16,FWilberforce looks back on his
OL,17,Fpolitical career and his first
OL,18,Fimpressions of William Pitt - who
OL,19,Feventually became Britain's youngest
OL,20,FPrime Minister.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781542111
OL,3,CLetters written by Hull-born William
OL,4,CWilberforce fetch #3.9k under the
OL,5,Chammer
OL,7,FWilberforce's efforts resulted in the
OL,8,FSlave Trade Act in 1807 which outlawed
OL,9,Fthe buying and selling of human beings
OL,10,Facross the British Empire.
OL,12,FIt took two decades for the Slavery
OL,13,FAbolition bill in 1833 to officially
OL,14,Fgrant freedom to all enslaved people
OL,15,Facross the empire, although slavery
OL,16,Fstill persisted in British territory
OL,17,Fin India and elsewhere for many more
OL,18,Fyears.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
