OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781542111
OL,3,CLetters written by Hull-born William
OL,4,CWilberforce fetch #3.9k under the
OL,5,Chammer
OL,7,FHe died in 1833, and heard the news of
OL,8,Fthe Slavery Abolition Bill on his
OL,9,Fdeathbed. Wilberforce was laid to rest
OL,10,Falongside William Pitt in Westminster
OL,11,FAbbey.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/8
